
                                            Black Friday shoppers and social media users say they are underwhelmed by the pricing as well as the items available on special.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - Black Friday hit South Africa as early as midnight.  While queues snaked as far as the eye could see and shoppers jostled for items in stores across the country, others feel the mayhem was not worth it. Online stores such as Takealot and Superbalist experienced serious technical issues. Injuries and damage to store properties have been reported in some places. And ... of course, social media reacted.           